    "summary": "I have extensive international experience in cash-, fx and risk management, coordinating closely with Corporate tax and HQ's Capital Markets, business units and other constituents regarding loan matters. Tracking capital funds allocated to business units, including new requests and cumulative investments over time.\n\n* Updating Multi Currency Credit Facilities\n* Euro Medium Term Note programmes\n* Debt Facilities, restructuring, terms and conditions\n* Reviewing and verifying Cross Currency/Interest Rate Swaps\n* Updating Multi Currency Commercial Paper programmes\n* Supervision and coordinating International Settlements\n* Daily Cash Management in all currencies\n* Monthly Liquidity reporting\n* FX Risk and Interest Rate Management\n\nSystem administration of key Treasury systems, including the Treasury workstations (SimCorp's International Treasurer, Wall Street Systems) and the cooporation's electronic banking systems.\n\nManaging for three international financial services companies their EMEA portfolio of over 400 intercompany loans, 250 swap contracts and more than 300 debt notes issues, with a combined balance sheet of over 15 billion Euros. \n\nActively contribute to and assist in various Treasury projects as needed in areas, such as Treasury systems. Take on other Treasury responsibilities as needed and act as backup for other departmental functions such as forecasting and foreign exchange.\n\nParticipated in an International Professional Development Scheme of Volkswagen AG Headquarters in Germany over a year.\n\nSpecialties: I have a professional way of looking at business activities, with a strong responsibility and a hands-on mentality.\nEasily switching between disciplines and resourceful.\nReliable with excellent communication skills, flexible and desire to learn.",
